The paper deals with the problem of embedding graphs on a grid, which is a common topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithm presented in the paper is based on the properties of 3-connected planar graphs, which are also studied in graph theory (cs.DS). The paper also involves combinatorial aspects, such as the requirement that the dual vertices be placed inside their corresponding primal faces, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The problem of embedding graphs on a grid is related to graph drawing and visualization, which is a topic in graph theory (cs.GT) and information science (cs.SI).
